<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-07-17T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-07-17T13:00:00-05:00" n="373" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d373">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">824.00/55: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Maginnis</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-07-17T14:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">July 17,
                                            1920—2 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>45. Your July 12, 6 p.m.</p>
                            <p>The Department desires you to keep it fully and closely informed of
                                all developments in the situation, particularly those affecting the
                                foreign policy of the Government now in control. You are instructed
                                to take no action which could be construed as constituting
                                recognition of the Provisional Government by the Government of the
                                United States.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>